[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10112] allowed for 
``.parq``
 file ending as alternative to 
``.parquet``
Hofer-Julian 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10111] added a notice to enable develop mode on Windows
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10110] renamed the Toolkit's 
``pretty-print-command``
rgwood 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10109] fixed watch not detecting modifications on Windows
ito-hiroki 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10102] fixed tab completion order of directories to be consistent with order of files
sholderbach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10095] removed illegal star dependency
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10073] removed global clippy 
``-A``
 from 
``toolkit.nu``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10072] removed clippy global 
``-A``
 from CI
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10071] polished 
``CONTRIBUTING``
, add Rust style
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10070] pinned reedline to 0.23.0
amtoine 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10087] removed Clippy flags from the PR template
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10055] reverted "deprecate 
``--format``
 and 
``--list``
 in 
``into datetime``
 (#10017)"
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10053] made the code page optional for 
``std clip``
kubouch 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10068] removed "let config" warning
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10049] recursively exported constants from modules
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10035] simplified virtualenv testing
horasal 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10030] added encoding auto-detection for 
``decode``
herobs 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9873] fixed 9156 endian consistency
nibon7 submitted 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9577] Don't use 
``oldtime``
 feature of chrono 
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9550] Use built-in is_terminal instead of is_terminal::is_terminal
